30/08/2005
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- A top Montenegrin police official was shot dead early Tuesday (30 August), according to local press reports in Podgorica. 
The deputy head of the criminal police department and head of the general crime department of the Montenegrin Interior Ministry, Slavoljub M. 
Scekic, was killed near his home at around 1 am local time. 
Witnesses said the gunman fired three times before fleeing in a getaway car. 
Police have detained more than 20 people so far. 
(Vijesti, Beta, B92 - 30/08/05)
